parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including headlight, turn signal, and brake light malfunctions, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.

Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including battery failure, headlight and taillight failures, and issues with the air conditioning and other systems. These failures can lead to safety risks, such as reduced visibility while driving, and can also cause inconvenience and financial losses.
